Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.62,0:00:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A racing second hand,\Na shooting comet!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.29,0:00:07.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan's logic works great on\Nhearts tired by modern society!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.02,0:00:10.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's case is a midsummer night!\NI crush the culprit's dreams!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.88,0:00:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.42,0:00:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.55,0:00:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.21,0:01:57.09,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Triplets Villa Murder Case
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.38,0:01:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Triplets Villa Murder Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.34,0:01:59.55,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Izu
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.34,0:02:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Summer! You got your sun and your ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.01,0:02:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I can't believe Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s\Nthe only boy on the beach
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.02,0:02:12.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when there's two hot girls here!\NHow pathetic!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.36,0:02:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.48,0:02:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Obviously! This is\Nyour villa's private beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.20,0:02:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.36,0:02:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're here to get a great tan\Nand catch guys all summer long!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.91,0:02:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're always talking\Nabout guys, Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.75,0:02:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be nice to know\Nwho your husband'll be!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.71,0:02:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bought that swimsuit to\Nshow Shinichi-{\i1}kun{\i0}, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.39,0:02:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That... was for me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.01,0:02:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I'm here,\NI'll get a closer look!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.02,0:02:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.40,0:02:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Young girls are so nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.06,0:02:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't have gotten engaged yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.06,0:02:56.94,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomizawa Yuzo (28) Ayako's Fiancé
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.23,0:03:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you! You're supposed\Nto be in love with my sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.82,0:03:01.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he's--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.91,0:03:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.91,0:03:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomizawa Yuzo-{\i1}san{\i0}, third son of\Nthe head of Tomizawa Industries!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.37,0:03:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's marrying my sister in the fall!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.17,0:03:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our two family\Ncompanies are really close!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.17,0:03:16.92,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomizawa Family Villa\NSuzuki Family Villa
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.92,0:03:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look! Even our villas are next to each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.92,0:03:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He saw my sister at a party\Nand had love at first sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.76,0:03:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're embarrassing me,\NSonoko-{\i1}chan{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.89,0:03:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's in our villa\Nif you're looking for her...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.93,0:03:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm here to introduce\Nher to my father and brothers!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.56,0:03:36.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.44,0:03:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.11,0:03:40.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. My brothers arrive tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.99,0:03:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but my father should be\Nat the villa by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.99,0:03:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give him a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.79,0:03:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Tomizawa residence.\NWe're not home right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.08,0:03:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so please leave a message\Nafter the beep--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.83,0:03:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? It's the machine...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.29,0:03:59.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.17,0:04:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,3:10...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.96,0:04:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's weird. He was\Nsupposed to be there at 3:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.68,0:04:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.97,0:04:10.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tetsuhara-{\i1}ojisama {\i0}is coming!\NThis is no time to play in the ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.93,0:04:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to greet him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.43,0:04:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.65,0:04:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.78,0:04:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.53,0:04:25.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Yuzo! I came over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.74,0:04:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh! I said to wait in the\Nvilla for me to bring her there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.58,0:04:33.87,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomizawa Tetsuhara (60) President
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.91,0:04:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we might enjoy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.83,0:04:37.54,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Suzuki Ayako- Sonoko's Sister
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.83,0:04:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your future wife's cooking tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.13,0:04:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sent it flying!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.50,0:04:46.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gone! Three runs! Kogure sent\Nit into the right stands in the rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.34,0:04:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.68,0:04:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad. You're sure\Na big Kogure fan...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.01,0:04:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sure am!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.47,0:04:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you didn't have\Nto watch him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.35,0:05:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no choice. I'm getting\Nbad satellite reception.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.40,0:05:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A pop fly down the center!\NThe Falcons are on fire now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.70,0:05:12.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 9:00, so we bring you\Na 5-minute news break!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.70,0:05:17.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Typhoon 11 has intensified and\Nis moving northward from Okinawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.67,0:05:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, many planes\Nand boats are delayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.71,0:05:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,9:00? It's only the 6th inning...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.13,0:05:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rain kept delaying the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.76,0:05:30.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayako-{\i1}san{\i0}. Might you have a radio?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.76,0:05:33.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like\Nthat game's on the radio...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.89,0:05:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now! It'll begin soon!\NHow about some coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.23,0:05:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suzuki women are so considerate!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.90,0:05:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo! You're one lucky guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.07,0:05:51.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My other two sons,\Non the other hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.74,0:05:57.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taichi, the oldest, ditched the\Nbusiness and became a novelist instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.62,0:05:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he's still single.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.67,0:06:02.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuji, the middle son,\Njoined the company
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.46,0:06:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but got engaged with some\Nnobody without my consent!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.63,0:06:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop talking bad about them!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.55,0:06:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You too, Yuzo!\NWith your stupid paintings and all!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.64,0:06:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.02,0:06:21.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be in my studio.\NI have an illustration to finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.44,0:06:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.32,0:06:26.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only he'd quit being\Nstubborn and join the business,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.15,0:06:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd give him a good position!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.37,0:06:37.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's over! The Falcons finally\Nwin 9-8 in the 11th inning!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.75,0:06:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Alright! Hurray!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.12,0:06:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the essence\Nof Falcons baseball!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.80,0:06:48.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, look at the time.\NI should get back to my villa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.93,0:06:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, Ayako-{\i1}san{\i0}.\NI'll bring my sons over tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.01,0:06:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.52,0:06:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.98,0:07:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez! I wonder if he plans to\Nwatch another night game tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.57,0:07:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's already 11:30. We should--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.28,0:07:11.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A power failure?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.32,0:07:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.28,0:07:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? The lights\Nare out in the other villa...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.50,0:07:19.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must've been the lightning!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.12,0:07:23.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.38,0:07:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.59,0:07:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.59,0:07:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's he doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.01,0:07:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yuzo-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.52,0:07:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.31,0:07:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.15,0:07:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.49,0:07:54.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn it! I lost him!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.70,0:07:58.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.12,0:08:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir! Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.38,0:08:09.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.72,0:08:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.34,0:08:21.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you witnessed Mr. Tomizawa\Nbeing murdered by his son Yuzo
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.39,0:08:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at 11:30 last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.23,0:08:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.27,0:08:29.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayako-{\i1}san{\i0}. What's all this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.36,0:08:31.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.78,0:08:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomizawa Yuzo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.20,0:08:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.45,0:08:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.99,0:08:39.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know full well\Nyou killed your own father!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.58,0:08:43.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! Dad?! That's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.37,0:08:46.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Let go! I didn't kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.79,0:08:48.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on, Yuzo?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.75,0:08:51.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuji-{\i1}niisan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.75,0:08:52.80,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomizawa Tatsuji (28) Office Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.21,0:08:52.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's all the ruckus?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.63,0:08:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taichi-{\i1}aniki{\i0}!\NLooks like something happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.43,0:08:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.43,0:09:01.22,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomizawa Taichi (28) Novelist
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.89,0:09:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need an idea for a new novel...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.22,0:09:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Triplets?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.02,0:09:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomizawa Yuzo! You're under\Narrest for the murder of your father!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.23,0:09:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective! Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.73,0:09:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We did see the killer's face...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.07,0:09:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...But we only\Nsaw his eyes and nose!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.16,0:09:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't know Yuzo-{\i1}san\N{\i0}had two identical twins!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.29,0:09:29.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means it was one of you three...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.71,0:09:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in Okinawa\Nlast night on a business trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.67,0:09:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I took the first flight out and\Nlanded at Haneda three hours ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.43,0:09:42.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The last flight to\NOkinawa leaves at 8:00 pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.76,0:09:45.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't have been\Nat the villa when it happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.89,0:09:47.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Check it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.89,0:09:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.60,0:09:51.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought Okinawa was--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.07,0:09:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Detective. I'm not\Nsure I can call it an alibi, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.40,0:09:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have two messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.49,0:10:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.41,0:10:04.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,3:10...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.16,0:10:08.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's weird. He was\Nsupposed to be there at 3:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.96,0:10:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,3:10 pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.88,0:10:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was me! I called from the beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.67,0:10:16.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, this is Taichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.51,0:10:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.17,0:10:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Glad to see the Falcons won, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.64,0:10:26.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kogure pulled that homer to\Nthe right in the bottom of the 6th!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.35,0:10:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a batter!\NWell, see you tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.98,0:10:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,11:34 pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.19,0:10:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,11:34 pm... The time\Nthe murder took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.61,0:10:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're certain it\Nhappened around 11:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.58,0:10:48.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I had checked the\Nclock before we saw the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.04,0:10:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't look like he did it!\NThat game was only on satellite!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.67,0:10:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It ended just after 11:25.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.76,0:11:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't have known how\Nit ended unless he watched it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.05,0:11:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Confirm that with the\NTV and radio stations! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.43,0:11:05.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.56,0:11:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, if neither of us is the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.85,0:11:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Yuzo's the only possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.06,0:11:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.56,0:11:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I'd never kill anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.07,0:11:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then where were you last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.82,0:11:19.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in my studio the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.94,0:11:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! A fellow illustrator called\Nand woke me up! Just after 11:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.08,0:11:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He woke you up?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.79,0:11:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.54,0:11:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I dozed off! I had to pull\Nan all-nighter to finish this job...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.12,0:11:35.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we'll check with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.25,0:11:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Yokomizo!\NAbout that passenger list...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.51,0:11:46.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? My name was there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.72,0:11:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.27,0:11:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The issue is the\Ntime the plane landed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.85,0:11:59.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The plane you were supposedly on\Nlanded at Haneda thirty minutes ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.28,0:12:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.94,0:12:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess the typhoon delayed it!\NThey said so on the news last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.16,0:12:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.95,0:12:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about you tell us\Nwhere you really were last night?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.50,0:12:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokyo! That's right!\NI returned to Tokyo last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.50,0:12:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To Hiromi's place in Tokyo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.55,0:12:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiromi?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.46,0:12:24.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My fiancée.\NI heard she had collapsed...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.47,0:12:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want my dad to\Nfind out I dropped work for her,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.43,0:12:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I had someone cover for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.60,0:12:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the truth! Please believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.56,0:12:35.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can anyone vouch for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.27,0:12:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.52,0:12:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! I just mentioned\Nhow the game ended!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.02,0:12:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No news programs\Nwere covering it at 11:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.32,0:12:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, because I flipped channels,\Nhoping to see that home run again!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.03,0:12:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Yokomizo.\NHe's telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.45,0:12:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was after midnight when TV\Nand radio stations covered the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.83,0:13:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, are you a fan of Kogure?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.76,0:13:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were praising him on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.13,0:13:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's awesome! Only he could\Nhit a home run into the right stands!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.85,0:13:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hit?! Explain yourself, Taichi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.31,0:13:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said he pulled it\Nto the right on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.44,0:13:20.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you really\Nwatching that game?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.03,0:13:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess the truth's out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.86,0:13:26.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you killed your father?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.70,0:13:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing of the sort! I meant\Nthat I didn't see the game on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.33,0:13:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I listened to it all on the\Nradio while playing {\i1}pachinko{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.63,0:13:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was taking a break from writing...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.17,0:13:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess the only radio broadcast\Nwas in Osaka, where I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.72,0:13:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right, only one radio station\Nin Osaka aired that game.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.05,0:13:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I left a message\Nat the time of the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.06,0:13:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.69,0:14:03.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?!\NOne of those three is lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.78,0:14:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the victim's\Nmissing watch bugs me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.07,0:14:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would the killer take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.41,0:14:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To keep the time a secret? Or--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.58,0:14:16.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? This VCR is blinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.33,0:14:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, there was a 10-minute\Nblackout at 11:30 last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.04,0:14:25.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah! There was a\Nblackout just before the murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.38,0:14:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A blackout?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.97,0:14:30.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, this is strange!\NWhat he said is impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.80,0:14:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And at the time, it was--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.39,0:14:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the watch\Ntaken from the victim was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.60,0:14:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.94,0:14:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt about it!\NThe killer is the one telling two lies!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.90,0:14:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.07,0:14:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to ask all three\Nof you down to the station!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.95,0:14:55.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.74,0:14:57.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, this isn't funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.50,0:14:59.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.16,0:15:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.29,0:15:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These folks saw the killer's\Nface just after the murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.92,0:15:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One that looked just like you three!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.34,0:15:15.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,\None of you killed your father!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.89,0:15:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know who did it! It's definitely\Nthe one with the strange alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.69,0:15:25.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! I'll knock Sonoko\Nout and make her a detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.27,0:15:28.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.40,0:15:31.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this watch?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.24,0:15:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.70,0:15:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.37,0:15:38.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was aiming a weird watch at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.08,0:15:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a toy!\NProfessor Agasa gave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.29,0:15:44.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A BB comes out if you press a button!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.92,0:15:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're such a troublemaker!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.71,0:15:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I gotta use the bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.31,0:16:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko?! Hey, Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.64,0:16:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've figured it out. I know that\Nhe killed Tetsuhara-{\i1}ojisama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.90,0:16:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not one of the\Nthree has a clear alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.70,0:16:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's one who's clearly lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.03,0:16:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer is Taichi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.54,0:16:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taichi-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.21,0:16:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.25,0:16:28.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting. But I was in\Nan Osaka {\i1}pachinko {\i0}parlor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.80,0:16:32.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think\NI could've been here then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.01,0:16:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A {\i1}pachinko{\i0} parlor at 11:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.22,0:16:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.68,0:16:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you know that {\i1}pachinko {\i0}parlors
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.06,0:16:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can only stay open until 11:00 pm?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.98,0:16:52.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, {\i1}pachinko {\i0}parlors are generally\Nforbidden to operate past 11:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.61,0:16:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even in Osaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.49,0:16:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means you're lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.87,0:16:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.33,0:17:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the broadcast in a taxi\Non my way home from the parlor...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.25,0:17:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.75,0:17:07.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be like that.\NIt was a simple mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.13,0:17:13.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I left a message\Nwhen the murder took place!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.01,0:17:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you explain that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.05,0:17:16.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.14,0:17:21.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the major oversight\Nyou made during the murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.72,0:17:23.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.68,0:17:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should know; you were there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.73,0:17:30.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The power went out\Nfor ten minutes at 11:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.36,0:17:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! The answering machine\Nwouldn't work without power!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.19,0:17:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its batteries power the clock,\Nbut it can't record messages!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.99,0:17:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what's your message\Ndoing there at 11:34?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.58,0:17:48.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you could ask\NYuzo the same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.88,0:17:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he got a call\Njust after 11:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.00,0:17:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know anything, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.01,0:17:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can still make calls\Nduring a power outage!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.76,0:18:00.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.26,0:18:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true. Telephones receive\Npower through the phone lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.14,0:18:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone must've messed with\Nthe clock to frame me--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.48,0:18:12.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no telling when you'd call.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.57,0:18:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody could've\Nmatched the times just right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.24,0:18:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, when the game ended,\Nyou left a message
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.07,0:18:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on the machine whose clock\Nyou had set ahead in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.58,0:18:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Glad to see the Falcons won, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.71,0:18:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As if you left the message\Njust when the murder happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.75,0:18:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you turned the clock back,\Nand waited for your father to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.26,0:18:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father, who came\Nnext door to see the game!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.39,0:18:44.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's when you killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.85,0:18:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I couldn't have\Nknown when he'd return!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.60,0:18:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you knew.\NYou used a transmitter to hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.11,0:18:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A transmitter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.11,0:19:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bugged your villa? Then go ahead\Nand look! There won't be any!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.49,0:19:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody said you bugged the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.62,0:19:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't there something unnaturally\Nmissing from the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.79,0:19:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.75,0:19:15.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aha! With a bugged watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.75,0:19:19.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he could keep tabs on\Nboth the victim and the game!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.97,0:19:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the watch was taken\Nto remove the evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.76,0:19:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.43,0:19:28.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bugging the victim's watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.14,0:19:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and breaking his satellite receiver\Nto make him come to my villa...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.86,0:19:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As his son, you could easily do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.65,0:19:43.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice theory. I almost\Nwant to use it for a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.32,0:19:46.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it'd be a third-rate novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.74,0:19:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any proof that I changed\Nthe answering machine's clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.91,0:19:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The times match; even\NYuzo's message had the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.80,0:20:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You talk big for having no proof--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.34,0:20:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit playin' around!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.05,0:20:07.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fake time and message\Non the answering machine
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.76,0:20:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,actually prove that you're the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.52,0:20:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.02,0:20:15.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be true!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.77,0:20:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! This must be a mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.61,0:20:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had no reason to kill Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.49,0:20:26.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that, Yuzo. I'm not the\Ngreat brother you take me for.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.20,0:20:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Money. I wanted the\Nold man's inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.62,0:20:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I could keep writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.79,0:20:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.21,0:20:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Things got tough. I suddenly\Nran out of work and money...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.96,0:20:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found out when\NI went to Dad for help...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.72,0:20:49.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He had pressured the publishers\Nto drop each job that came my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.22,0:20:55.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he wanted me to\Nquit and follow in his footsteps.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.48,0:20:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then you--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.27,0:21:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I used his\Nvisit here to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.65,0:21:08.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's also why I sent him the\Nbugged watch and broke his receiver.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.45,0:21:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzo. I was going\Nto try pinning it on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.33,0:21:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To increase my\Nshare of the inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.83,0:21:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was all so I could\Nkeep writing my novels...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.42,0:21:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it seems I wrote a poor mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.05,0:21:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think the power\Nwould go out just then...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.35,0:21:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess fact is\Nstranger than fiction...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.27,0:21:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I didn't have the\Nskill to be a writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.32,0:23:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with Sonoko?\NShe's spacing out...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.49,0:23:20.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's probably relieved\NYuzo-{\i1}san {\i0}wasn't the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.63,0:23:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh oh. She's staring at her arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.25,0:23:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me she noticed\NI shot a sleeping dart in it...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.17,0:23:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I failed...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.22,0:23:34.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you talking about?\NThat was great detective work!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.01,0:23:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective work?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.35,0:23:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just look at my arm!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.35,0:23:39.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's totally white!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.93,0:23:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was supposed to get a tan\Nand catch some guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.36,0:23:49.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, Ran!\NLet's go to a tanning salon!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.94,0:23:54.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not now! We have to give our\Nstatements at the police station!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.07,0:23:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.87,0:23:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a dumb girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.41,0:24:25.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.21,0:24:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.21,0:24:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an SOS!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.37,0:24:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone out of the boat!\NThe tide's rising!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.47,0:24:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The waves are\Ntoo high for us to swim out!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.35,0:24:22.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn it! This is like a maze!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.48,0:24:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which way?! Which way do we go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.44,0:24:31.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Junior Detective League Shipwreck Case
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.02,0:24:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.52,0:24:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Junior Detective League Shipwreck Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.02,0:24:49.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.25,0:24:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Tide's Ebb and Flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.70,0:24:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode the Detective Boys make an appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.45,0:24:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.92,0:24:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Genta.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.53,0:24:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Mitsuhiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.25,0:24:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.64,0:25:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
